5: I'm thinking of getting a job.
9:
D-do you have a fever? Hurry, we
need to find a doctor—
18:
With the way you normally act? I
don't think so.
21:
So why the sudden passion for
working?
24:
Well, you know how my Prince
Charming has been keeping me
waiting?
27:
I figured I'd speed up the process by
putting myself out there to find.
32:
The Oculus, first issue... "How to Meet
Your Prince Charming—a Must Read
for Palpebra Gals."
35:
According to that, the most popular
place to meet your beloved is at
work. Which means I need a job.
39:
I'm not entirely sure this is a good
idea...
43:
You seriously think you can get a job
with a bed head like that?
49:
I'll have you know that I tried to fix it,
but this is the best I could manage
on my own.
54:
Well... You could always go to a
salon in Palpebra.
61:
I read in the Oculus that salon
stylists are positive, cheery
people—the exact opposite of me.
65:
I could never carry a conversation
with them. Trying to do so for hours
would be like a slow form of torture...
69:
It's always something or other with
you...
73:
...But you make a good point about
my hair. I need to make it
presentable.
77:
Fine. I... I suppose I'll do it! I'll go to the
salon!
81:
Oh! I'm guessing you're our next
appointment. Ruelle, right?
86: Y-yes! S-sorry to keep you waiting!
90: ...You sure this was a good idea?
93:
Eh. Too late to take it back either
way.
104:
Hehe, thanks. That stylist really knew
what he was doing. Ehehe... He was
so dreamy...
108:
...Don't tell me you fell for the first
schmuck that was nice to you.
112:
Wow. Rude. It's not like my opinion of
stylists suddenly changed or
anything. They're too flashy for me.
115:
...But that guy was different from the
rest.
117:
He was extremely kind to me,
complimenting my hair and making
sure the conversation was easy to
follow. I bet I'm the only one who—
121:
...You totally fell for the first schmuck
that was nice to you.
125:
Oh. You know what? I just realized...
He's the Prince Charming I've been
waiting for all along.
129:
Take a look at this. It's an
advertisement for a cake shop
looking for part-time employees.
133:
The place happens to be right
across from the salon. There's no
way this is just simple
coincidence—it must be fate!
142:
Anyway, I'm off to have my interview
there!
149:
Listen, kid, you really gotta turn up
the charm. I'm begging you.
156:
Wh-why am I having so much
trouble now? I was speaking just fine
at the salon...
164:
Oh, you're the girl that just came to
the salon. I didn't know you worked
here.
167:
Ehe... I-I only started today... What,
um... What are you looking for?
171:
A birthday cake. It's actually my
girlfriend's birthday today...
191:
Ruelle, would you mind getting up
from under there? I'd really like to
start cleaning.
195:
No... This is my dark fortress now. I'm
never going outside again.
201:
...Ha. Haha. If only I'd never gone
outside. None of this would've
happened.
204:
...We all have some bad luck every
once in a while.
206:
Next time will be different. So come
out, Ruelle.
213:
I'm done looking for my beloved out
there.
216:
I was an idiot for thinking I'd
compromise and search them out!
It's totally not romantic at all!
219:
I'll wait from now on... Even if the
world ends around me.
221:
So come find me, my Prince
Charming! No more delays!
242:
I hope my Prince Charming comes
soon.
